Olam to Invest $50 Million in Mozambican Cotton Project, Noticias Reports

-- B y   F r e d   K a t e r e r e
-- 
2011-08-05T06:20:44Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-05/olam-to-invest-50-million-in-mozambican-cotton-project-noticias-reports.html
Olam International Ltd. (OLAM) ’s  Mozambique 
unit will invest $50 Million in cotton production in northern
Nampula province, Noticias reported, citing Antonio Alberto, a
senior official at Mozambique’s cotton institute.  The investment will improve growing and processing of the
crop and boost production in the region to 25,000 metric tons
from 18,000 tons, the Mapoputo-based newspaper cited Alberto as
saying.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Fred Katerere in Maputo at 
 fkaterere@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gordon Bell at 
 gbell16@bloomberg.net  